http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/bangalore/Narrow-escape-for-passengers-as-BMTC-bus-catches-fire/article14009924.ece

As many as 20 passengers had a narrow escape after a BMTC bus accidentally caught fire due to short circuit at Kempegowda Bus stand on Tuesday afternoon.The driver noticed smoke from the engine and immediately asked the passengers to alight.Commotion prevailed for a while at the bus stand after the incident.“The bus was parked at the platform no 22 and was ready to leave when the fire broke out. I immediately alerted the fire and emergency services control room,” said Murthy, an eyewitness and BMTC employee.A call was received at the Fire and Emergency Services control room around 12.15 pm, following which two fire tenders from High grounds and North zone were immediately pressed into the services.“Preliminary reports suggest that an electrical short circuit in the battery caused the fire. In about half an hour, the fire was put out. According to initial estimates, the loss is approximately Rs. 50 lakh,” a senior fire officer said.